# Nova environment variables — SECRET INVENTORY
#
# ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
# │  Secrets are managed in Doppler (project: nova, config: prd).  │
# │  This file is a REFERENCE for which env vars exist.            │
# │  Do NOT create a config/env file — use `doppler run --`.       │
# │                                                                │
# │  Manage secrets:  doppler secrets --project nova --config prd  │
# │  Run with secrets: doppler run -- nv <command>                 │
# └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
#
# ── Core Secrets (loaded by Secrets::from_env()) ──────────────────
#
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY          — Direct API calls (optional, CLI uses OAuth)
# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN         — Telegram bot authentication
# DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN          — Discord bot authentication
# BLUEBUBBLES_PASSWORD       — BlueBubbles iMessage bridge
# MS_GRAPH_CLIENT_ID         — Azure AD app for Teams/email
# MS_GRAPH_CLIENT_SECRET     — Azure AD app secret
# MS_GRAPH_TENANT_ID         — Azure AD tenant ID
# JIRA_API_TOKEN             — Default Jira API token (fallback)
# JIRA_USERNAME              — Default Jira username (fallback)
# JIRA_API_TOKEN_{INSTANCE}  — Instance-qualified (e.g. _PERSONAL, _LLC)
# JIRA_USERNAME_{INSTANCE}   — Instance-qualified
# ELEVENLABS_API_KEY         — Text-to-speech API key
# GOOGLE_CALENDAR_CREDENTIALS — Base64-encoded service account JSON
#
# ── Tool Client Secrets (loaded on-demand via from_env()) ─────────
#
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY          — Stripe API access
# VERCEL_TOKEN               — Vercel API access
# SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN           — Sentry error tracking
# SENTRY_ORG                 — Sentry organization slug
# RESEND_API_KEY             — Resend email API
# HA_TOKEN                   — Home Assistant API
# HA_URL                     — Home Assistant URL (default: http://localhost:8123)
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL     — Upstash Redis REST endpoint
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN   — Upstash Redis auth token
# ADO_ORG                    — Azure DevOps organization name
# ADO_PAT                    — Azure DevOps personal access token
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN       — Cloudflare API token
# DOPPLER_API_TOKEN          — Doppler secrets management
# NEON_API_KEY               — Neon platform management API
# POSTGRES_URL_{CODE}        — Per-project Neon DB connection (e.g. _OO, _TC)
# PLAID_DB_URL               — Local Postgres with Plaid sync data
# POSTHOG_API_KEY            — PostHog analytics API
# POSTHOG_HOST               — PostHog host (default: app.posthog.com)
# POSTHOG_PROJECT_ID         — Default PostHog project ID
# POSTHOG_PROJECT_{CODE}     — Per-project PostHog project ID (e.g. _OO)
